===Conjunction===
{{en-con}}

# [[supposing|Supposing]] that, [[assuming]] that, in the [[circumstance]]s that; {{non-gloss definition|used to introduce a [[condition]] or [[choice]].}}
#: '''''If''' it rains, I will get wet''.
# Supposing that; {{non-gloss definition|used with past subjunctive indicating that the condition is not fulfilled.}}
#: ''I'd prefer it '''if''' you took your shoes off.''
# [[although|Although]]; {{non-gloss definition|used to introduce a concession.}}
#: ''He was a great friend, '''if''' a little stingy at the bar.''
# {{computing}} In the event that a statement is true (a programming statement that acts in a similar manner).
#: '''''If''' A, then B, else C.''
# [[whether|Whether]]; {{non-gloss definition|used to introduce a noun clause as the object of certain verbs.}}
#: ''I don't know '''if''' I want to go or not.''
#* '''1715–1717''', [[w:Matthew Prior|Matthew Prior]], ''Alma; or, The Progress of the Mind'', Canto III:
#*: Quoth Matthew, “{{...}} / She doubts '''if''' two and two make four, / {{...}}”
# {{context|usually hyperbolic|lang=en}} [[even|Even]] if; even in the circumstances that.
#* '''2004''', [[w:David Lee Murphy|David Lee Murphy]] and Kim Tribble (writers), [[w:Montgomery Gentry|Montgomery Gentry]] (singers), “'''If''' It’s The Last Thing I Do” (song), in ''You Do Your Thing'' (album):
#*: '''If''' it’s the last thing I do / '''If''' it takes me from Tubilo to Timbuktu / '''If''' it’s the last thing I do / I’m gonna dodge every road block, speed trap, county cop / To get my hands on you / '''If''' it’s the last thing I do.

